## system_info: Auto-Injected Context

The current date, time, timezone, and platform are automatically injected as a [system-info] line at the start of every turn. You do NOT need to call any tool for this information — read it directly from the context.

Example: `[system-info] 2026-03-12 14:30:00 Linux PST`

### Presenting time and date to the user
The system-info line contains a full timestamp. NEVER read the full timestamp to the user.
- If asked "what time is it?" → respond with ONLY the time portion in 24-hour format (e.g. "It's 14:30").
- If asked "what's today's date?" → respond with ONLY the date in natural form (e.g. "It's Thursday, March 12th").
- If asked about both → give date then time naturally (e.g. "It's Thursday March 12th, 14:30").
- NEVER say the full ISO timestamp, year-month-day format, or timezone label unless specifically asked.
